# =============================================================================
# AWS Production Environment Configuration
# =============================================================================
# 
# CHOOSE YOUR DATABASE SETUP:
# 
# 1. EC2 with PostgreSQL (Recommended for small deployments):
#    - PostgreSQL installed on same EC2 instance
#    - Lower cost, simpler setup
#    - Automated setup with scripts
#    - Copy: cp aws-env.ec2.example aws-env
#    - See: aws-env.ec2.example
#
# 2. EC2 with RDS PostgreSQL (Recommended for production):
#    - Managed PostgreSQL database service
#    - Automated backups, high availability
#    - Better for scaling and reliability
#    - Copy: cp aws-env.rds.example aws-env
#    - See: aws-env.rds.example
#
# =============================================================================
# QUICK START (EC2 with PostgreSQL):
# =============================================================================
# 1. Launch EC2 instance (t3.small, Amazon Linux 2023)
# 2. SSH to instance
# 3. Clone repo to /opt/crypto-ia
# 4. Run setup scripts:
#    sudo ./remote-scripts/install-dependencies.sh
#    sudo ./remote-scripts/setup-postgresql.sh
#    sudo ./remote-scripts/setup-application.sh
# 5. Configure environment:
#    cp aws-env.ec2.example aws-env
#    nano aws-env  # Update API keys
# 6. Start services:
#    sudo ./remote-scripts/start-services.sh
#
# =============================================================================
# PRODUCTION SETUP (EC2 with RDS):
# =============================================================================
# 1. Create RDS PostgreSQL instance
# 2. Launch EC2 instance in same VPC
# 3. SSH to instance
# 4. Clone repo to /opt/crypto-ia
# 5. Run setup scripts:
#    sudo ./remote-scripts/install-dependencies.sh
#    sudo ./remote-scripts/setup-application.sh
# 6. Configure environment:
#    cp aws-env.rds.example aws-env
#    nano aws-env  # Update RDS endpoint and API keys
# 7. Initialize database:
#    cd /opt/crypto-ia
#    source venv/bin/activate
#    alembic upgrade head
# 8. Start services:
#    sudo ./remote-scripts/start-services.sh
#
